news.title: Property rates in top 13 cities rise 19 per cent in Q3: Magicbricks Propindex Report
news.para: The affordable housing market saw strong growth in Ahmedabad (62%) and Kolkata (48%) while luxury properties were most searched in the Mumbai Metropolitan Region (90%), New Delhi (58%), and Gurugram (48%).

news.title: Deadline looms, just 78,000 property tags issued in Delhi
news.para: MCD has around 14 lakh taxpayers and around 13 lakh properties have been issued the unique property identification code (UPIC) number.

news.title: Mumbai: 24-acre Bandra sprawl put up for development, builder must be worth Rs 15,000 crore
news.para: “The biggest builders will find themselves ineligible to bid. It looks like the tender has been tailor-made for a select few,’’ said a developer, whose representative attended the pre-bid meeting.

news.title: Gurugram: Structural audit of 22 highrises held up as builders yet to pay fee
news.para: A total of 23 highrise societies were selected for the second phase of structural audit, but only one has paid the fee so far.

news.title: Homefirst Finance net profit jumps 34% to Rs 79 crore in Q3 FY24
news.para: Homefirst Finance said in a statement its quarterly disbursement grew over 29 per cent to Rs 1,007 crore, taking the total loan book higher by 33.5 per cent to Rs 9,014 crore in the December quarter.

news.title: Sebi issues demand notices to DHFL's former promoters in disclosure rule violation case
news.para: The demand notices came after the Wadhawans failed to pay the fine imposed on them by the Securities and Exchange Board of India (Sebi) in July 2023.

news.title: Lessor has to pay GST on rent if property is used for commercial purposes
news.para: In the case of Deepak Jain (the applicant) who had leased out his property to a private limited company, which was engaged in back-office operations, the AAR observed that, up to July 17, 2022, renting of residential dwellings for use as a residence was exempt from GST, while renting for commercial use was taxable at 18%.

news.title: Aurum PropTech losses widen to Rs 21.32 crore in Oct-Dec quarter
news.para: Total income, however, increased to Rs 62.09 crore during October-December period of this fiscal, from Rs 41.15 crore in the corresponding period of the previous year, according to a regulatory filing.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh CM disburses Rs 47 crore interest reimbursement under housing scheme
news.para: As banks are providing housing loans at nine to 11 per cent interest rates, the state government has decided to reimburse interest over and above three per cent to reduce the financial burden of the beneficiaries.

news.title: China's Country Garden nears full exit from Australia with residential project sale
news.para: Australian subsidiary Risland had agreed to sell its partial interest in most of the Wilton Greens development, some 330 hectares located about 65 km (40 miles) southwest of Sydney, according to an undated statement reviewed by Reuters on Thursday.

news.title: Polycab India net profit rises 15% to Rs 416 crore in Q3 FY24
news.para: Its revenue from operations rose 16.83 per cent to Rs 4,340.47 crore in the third quarter of the current fiscal, up from Rs 3,715.18 crore in the year-ago period.

news.title: Edelweiss fund to provide Rs 350 crore debt to Adarsh Developers entity
news.para: Shreshta Infra, an Adarsh Developers' special purpose vehicle, plans to on-lend Rs 200 crore to its affiliates and allocate the remaining Rs 150 crore for project financing and general corporate purposes, providing a financial blueprint for future real estate ventures.

news.title: Hyderabad: Three years on, pattadar passbooks not yet issued for 18 lakh acres
news.para: With 16 lakh acres of land in Hyderabad Metropolitan Development Authority districts such as Rangareddy, Medchal Malkajgiri and Sangareddy lying idle thanks to the Dharani prohibited list, urban planners and experts expressed concern over one of the major economic resources going waste.

news.title: Give 64 acres in Mulund for rental homes for Dharavi squatters, Maharashtra tells BMC
news.para: The letter says DRPPL has to build rental housing for residents found ineligible for free housing. “Rental housing is to be constructed for around 3-4 lakh ineligible people,” it says.

news.title: Bengaluru: Site allotment process begins in new BDA layout after eight years
news.para: Announcing this on Wednesday, deputy chief minister DK Shivakumar said following a review meeting with BDA officials that after giving priority to landowners who had lost their land for the project, the government agency will be left with about 10,000 sites for sale.

news.title: Land records in 236 taluks of state being digitised: Karnataka revenue minister
news.para: It’s aimed at curbing fraudulent property transactions, he stated, adding that it avoids forgery through the manipulation of land records.

news.title: DDA invites buyers in phase-II e-auction
news.para: While the registration and submission of the earnest money deposit (EMD) will start at 11am, the last date of the online registration and the submission of online EMD is Jan 29, said an official.

news.title: Cement producers to see 80-100% surge in profits for December quarter
news.para: After clocking double-digit volume expansion in the first half of the year, growth of these companies in Oct-Dec is seen moderating to around 5-6% for most players due to elections in some states, a construction ban in the NCR region and shortage of labor.

news.title: Now, pay stamp duty on carpet area for homes in West Bengal
news.para: According to RERA, real estate players had to sell flats as per carpet area. Earlier, in the state flats and houses had to be registered as per super built area.

news.title: MahaRERA mandates single registration number for each standalone project
news.para: The regulatory authority has introduced this measure in response to certain cases where developers secured two or more MahaRERA registration numbers for the same or portions of a real estate project.
